Annotation.note:
A problem posed at International Mathematical Olympiad:
Show that the distance $d$ between the centers of the inscribed and the circumscribed circles of a triangle $\Delta\,ABC$ satisfies $d^2=r^2-2r\rho$, where $r$ is the radius of the circumscribed circle and $\rho$ the radius of the inscribed circle.
\begin{keywords} geometry theorem proving \end{keywords}
